description.narrative: Significant progress has been made towards policy and strategy formulation with the finalization of the National Plan for Elimination of Mother-to-Child Transmission of HIV, Syphilis and Hepatitis B (2020/21-2023/24), dissemination of the Consolidated HIV Guidelines and the HIV and COVID guidelines. The targeted number of Health Facilities providing pediatric ART exceeded the target with 406 facilities out of the targeted 306 offering ART to pregnant women living with HIV. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/08/2020
